From: OctaneOS <build@gameoctane.com>
Date: Sun, 06 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] power: mfd: axp2101: add AXP8191 poweroff support

axp20x_power_off() writes AXP20X_OFF (0x80) to AXP20X_OFF_CTRL (0x32).
On AXP8191, register 0x32 is AXP8191_CLDO4OUT_VOL (LDO4 voltage control),
not a poweroff register. The write is silently ignored and the board stays
powered on after Linux halts.

AXP8191 initiates a power-down sequence via register
AXP8191_POWER_DISABLE_POWER_DOWN_SEQUENCE (0x55). Add an AXP8191_ID branch
to use the correct register before falling through to the generic path.

---
 bsp/drivers/power/mfd/axp2101.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/bsp/drivers/power/mfd/axp2101.c b/bsp/drivers/power/mfd/axp2101.c
index aaaaaa1..bbbbbbb 100644
--- a/bsp/drivers/power/mfd/axp2101.c
+++ b/bsp/drivers/power/mfd/axp2101.c
@@ -3522,6 +3522,13 @@ static void axp20x_power_off(void)
 	if (axp20x_pm_power_off->variant == AXP288_ID)
 		return;

+	if (axp20x_pm_power_off->variant == AXP8191_ID) {
+		regmap_write(axp20x_pm_power_off->regmap,
+			     AXP8191_POWER_DISABLE_POWER_DOWN_SEQUENCE,
+			     AXP20X_OFF);
+		msleep(500);
+		return;
+	}
+
 	regmap_write(axp20x_pm_power_off->regmap, AXP20X_OFF_CTRL,
 		     AXP20X_OFF);
